    {
      "id": "1ktctgwvp",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "A chloro compound \"A\".<br><br>(i) forms aldehydes on ozonolysis followed by the hydrolysis.<br><br>(ii) when vaporized completely 1.53 g of A, gives 448 mL of vapour at STP.<br><br>The number of carbon atoms in a molecule of compound A is ___________.",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "haloalkanes",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "448 ml of A $$\\Rightarrow$$ 1.53 gm A<br><br>22400 ml of A $$\\Rightarrow$$ $${{1.53} \\over {448}}$$ $$\\times$$ 22400 gm A = 76.5 Agm<br><br>$$\\mathop {{H_3}CHC - CH - Cl}\\limits_{It\\,has\\,3\\,carbon\\,atoms} \\mathrel{\\mathop{\\kern0pt\\longrightarrow}\n\\limits_{Zn/{H_2}O}^{{O_3}}} \\mathop {C{H_3} - CH = O}\\limits_{Aldehyde} $$<br><br>&amp; MM is 36 + 5 + 35.5 = 76.5",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
