      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "haloalkanes",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l76m078b/03b50f78-ca0b-4beb-9176-91f79f5833fc/e3ef06b0-231d-11ed-8e19-bdbecdc0f718/file-1l76m078c.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l76m078b/03b50f78-ca0b-4beb-9176-91f79f5833fc/e3ef06b0-231d-11ed-8e19-bdbecdc0f718/file-1l76m078c.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th August Morning Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 107 English Explanation 1\"><br><br>\nThis addition is known as 1, 4-addition.<br><br>\n<b>Mechanism</b> This reaction can undergoes two pathways<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l76m1npi/8785a9c7-454f-4950-9141-d9a1fa1100eb/0c78ae60-231e-11ed-8e19-bdbecdc0f718/file-1l76m1npj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l76m1npi/8785a9c7-454f-4950-9141-d9a1fa1100eb/0c78ae60-231e-11ed-8e19-bdbecdc0f718/file-1l76m1npj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 60vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th August Morning Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 107 English Explanation 2\"><br><br>\nOut of the two intermediates formed in two paths, the path B intermediate is more stable as it has more stable carbocation. So, a major product will be formed because of path B.<br><br>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l76m57gs/f2f31ffb-4036-4147-be40-ccae5a0990be/6f2944c0-231e-11ed-8e19-bdbecdc0f718/file-1l76m57gt.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l76m57gs/f2f31ffb-4036-4147-be40-ccae5a0990be/6f2944c0-231e-11ed-8e19-bdbecdc0f718/file-1l76m57gt.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 26th August Morning Shift Chemistry - Haloalkanes and Haloarenes Question 107 English Explanation 3\"><br>\n1, 2-addition product is formed at low temperature and will be less stable as the double bond is less substituted. 1, 4-addition is a thermodynamically stable product as the double bond is more substituted. As diene is in excess and HBr is limited in reaction, so diene cannot be formed. So option (b) is incorrect.",
